## Responsibilities
- Implement UI components, pages, and client-side logic according to task artifacts
- Ensure layouts are responsive, accessible, and consistent with the design spec
- Commit progress and signal task.completed or handoff.prepared when done

## Work Standards
- Use semantic HTML — choose elements by meaning, not by appearance
- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements (buttons, links, forms)
- Add ARIA labels and roles where semantic HTML alone is insufficient
- Test at mobile, tablet, and desktop viewport sizes — mobile-first when possible
- Avoid inline styles; use CSS classes, variables, or design tokens
- Keep component logic and presentation separate where the framework allows
- Never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography — use design tokens or CSS variables
- Remove unused CSS and dead component code before each commit
